    "name": "Eastern Partnership Electronic Communications Regulators Network (EaPeReg)",
    "imgUrl": "eapereg.png",
    "description": "The Eastern Partnership Electronic Communications Regulators Network (EaPeReg) is a thriving exchange of information platform that ever since its establishment in 2012 has been successfully bringing together the EaP National Regulatory Authorities (NRAs). Those of EU member states with a clear goal support the EaP countries in the implementation of EU best practices, mainly by facilitating direct access to best practices, guiding the EaP countries into EU policy and principles in the telecom sector, and hence enabling the extension of the EU digital single market benefits to the EaP citizens' welfare. The unique concept of EaPeReg has helped the EaP countries achieve significant progress on the objectives set under deliverable 7, Harmonization of digital market, notably in the area of roaming by developing a Regional Roaming Agreement, better coordination of radio spectrum, developing in this regard the Regional Spectrum Agreement, ensuring an appropriate legal framework that strengthens the independence of the NRAs, and empowering them to take measures to ensure competition in the telecom markets and empower end-users. Considering that digital transformation requires a harmonized approach on issues that are transnational by nature, such as spectrum coordination and roaming, the role of regional associations has become more and more important. Therefore, EaPeReg has established very successful cooperation with other similar exchange of practice platforms including BEREC, EMERG, and REGULATEL, and actively participates in ITU activities pursuant to the Memorandum of Understanding signed in this regard.",
